    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean i know you have to say that but i've read a lot about how medical grade honey is actually used in hospitals for wound healing because it's so antibacterial. if i use the good stuff and keep it covered, isnt that basically the same thing as what a doctor would do? it seems like overkill to drive all the way to the ER just for a cut that might just need a bit of time to close up.",
